Infra Automation with Terraform + Ansible + Docker App

Project Goal
  Use Terraform to provision infra:

      - 2 EC2 instances inside a custom VPC
      - A security group allowing SSH (22), HTTP (80)
      - An Application Load Balancer (ALB) that balances traffic between the 2 EC2s


  Use Ansible to: 

      - Install Docker on both EC2s
      - Deploy a sample Flask Docker app


Architecture :

               +---------------------+
               |   AWS Load Balancer |
               +----------+----------+
                          |
                 -----------------
                 |               |
         +-------+-------+ +-----+-------+
         |   EC2 Instance | | EC2 Instance |
         |   (Docker)     | |   (Docker)   |
         |  Flask App     | |  Flask App   |
         +---------------+ +---------------+


Folder structure :

infra-project/
  ├── terraform/
  │   ├── main.tf
  │   ├── variables.tf
  │   └── outputs.tf
  └── ansible/
      ├── inventory.ini
      └── playbook.yml
      └── flask-app/
          ├── app.py
          └── Dockerfile


✅ Final Outcome

    Terraform provisions:
          VPC, subnet, security groups
          2 EC2 instances + Application Load Balancer

    Ansible configures:

         Docker installed on both servers
         Flask app deployed in Docker containers

    Visiting ALB DNS name → serves the Flask app, load-balanced between 2 EC2s